{"id":1014310862,"question_id":2856,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"10 months, 1 week","timestamp":1691377700,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"7 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1014310862/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Count Complete Subarrays in an Array","memory":"43.7 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int countCompleteSubarrays(int[] nums) {\n        int len = nums.length;\n        \n        HashSet<Integer> set= new HashSet<>();\n        for(int n: nums){\n            set.add(n);\n        }\n        \n        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map =new HashMap<>();\n        \n        int res = 0;\n        \n        int st =0;\n        for(int ed = 0; ed<len; ed++){\n            \n            map.put(nums[ed], map.getOrDefault(nums[ed], 0)+1);\n            if(map.size()<set.size())\n                continue;\n            \n            res+= len-ed;\n            \n            while(map.size()==set.size()){\n                map.put(nums[st], map.get(nums[st])-1);\n                if(map.get(nums[st])==0)\n                    map.remove(nums[st]);\n                st++;\n                \n                if(map.size()==set.size()){\n                    res+=len-ed;                    \n                }\n\n            }\n        }\n       \n        return res;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"count-complete-subarrays-in-an-array","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
